data.content:
## What Changed

.NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **OpenAPI.NET v2.0**, which has several breaking changes to the object model:

### 1. `OpenApiString` / `IOpenApiAny` → `JsonNode`

The entire `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace is gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` instead:

```csharp
// Before
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

### 2. `schema.Nullable` → `JsonSchemaType.Null` flag

`Nullable` was removed. Nullability is now a flag on `schema.Type`:

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After — remove the Null flag from Type
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

### 3. `OpenApiReference` + `OpenApiSecurityScheme` → `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference`

Dedicated reference types replace the generic `OpenApiReference` pattern:

```csharp
// Before
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// After
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};
```

### Full corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of namespace changes:**
| Removed | Replacement |
|---|---|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | `System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. | `JsonValue.Create(...)` |
| `OpenApiSecurityScheme` + `OpenApiReference` | `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` (in `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References`) |
| `schema.Nullable = bool` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` / `schema.Type |= JsonSchemaType.Null` |
